"{\"uid\": \"aljazeera.com-opinions-2024-7-29-paris-olympics-opening-ceremony-was-an-insult-to-women\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Men parading around as caricatures of women do not communicate love and inclusion.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 82, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Men\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 3}, {\"ngram\": \"caricatures\", \"from\": 23, \"to\": 34}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 38, \"to\": 43}, {\"ngram\": \"love\", \"from\": 63, \"to\": 67}, {\"ngram\": \"inclusion\", \"from\": 72, \"to\": 81}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Journalist, author and feminist campaigner.\", \"from\": 84, \"to\": 127, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Journalist\", \"from\": 84, \"to\": 94}, {\"ngram\": \"author\", \"from\": 96, \"to\": 102}, {\"ngram\": \"feminist campaigner\", \"from\": 107, \"to\": 126}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Save Share I was really looking forward to the opening ceremony of the 2024 Olympic Games in Paris.\", \"from\": 129, \"to\": 230, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 224, \"end\": 229, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.715056926133325e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 172, \"to\": 192}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Olympic Games\", \"from\": 196, \"to\": 218}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I love a big spectacle - I still remember the 2008 opening ceremony in Beijing, which has been deemed \\\"the greatest ever\\\" by many owing to its grand extravagances.\", \"from\": 231, \"to\": 394, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 302, \"end\": 309, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beijing\", \"score\": 0.9975920937759489, \"rank\": 0.002385580464170288, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beijing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beijing\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a big spectacle\", \"from\": 238, \"to\": 253}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2008 opening ceremony\", \"from\": 273, \"to\": 298}, {\"ngram\": \"its grand extravagances\", \"from\": 370, \"to\": 393}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And of course the one in London, in July 2012, which included everything, from politics to humour and great music, and successfully presented the very essence of Britain to millions of viewers across the world.\", \"from\": 395, \"to\": 605, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 420, \"end\": 426, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.999894729297719, \"rank\": 0.00010528178184494273, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 557, \"end\": 564, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.999937568879288, \"rank\": 3.2761636101196476e-05, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"course\", \"from\": 402, \"to\": 408}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 431, \"to\": 435}, {\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 457, \"to\": 467}, {\"ngram\": \"politics\", \"from\": 474, \"to\": 482}, {\"ngram\": \"humour\", \"from\": 486, \"to\": 492}, {\"ngram\": \"great music\", \"from\": 497, \"to\": 508}, {\"ngram\": \"the very essence\", \"from\": 537, \"to\": 553}, {\"ngram\": \"millions\", \"from\": 568, \"to\": 576}, {\"ngram\": \"viewers\", \"from\": 580, \"to\": 587}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 595, \"to\": 604}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I loved it all, and this is why, last Friday, I could hardly contain my excitement as I sat in front of my TV to see what Paris had to offer this year.\", \"from\": 607, \"to\": 758, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 729, \"end\": 734, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.715056926133325e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"my excitement\", \"from\": 676, \"to\": 689}, {\"ngram\": \"front\", \"from\": 702, \"to\": 707}, {\"ngram\": \"my TV\", \"from\": 711, \"to\": 716}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Theceremony, for lack of a better word, was a crashing disappointment.\", \"from\": 768, \"to\": 838, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Theceremony\", \"from\": 768, \"to\": 779}, {\"ngram\": \"lack\", \"from\": 785, \"to\": 789}, {\"ngram\": \"a better word\", \"from\": 793, \"to\": 806}, {\"ngram\": \"a crashing disappointment\", \"from\": 812, \"to\": 837}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It wasn't just the rain that dampened proceedings, but the perplexing artistic choices made by the organisers, and the lacklustre performances of so many of the people involved.\", \"from\": 839, \"to\": 1016, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"just the rain\", \"from\": 849, \"to\": 862}, {\"ngram\": \"the perplexing artistic choices\", \"from\": 894, \"to\": 925}, {\"ngram\": \"the organisers\", \"from\": 934, \"to\": 948}, {\"ngram\": \"the lacklustre performances\", \"from\": 954, \"to\": 981}, {\"ngram\": \"the people\", \"from\": 996, \"to\": 1006}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French media said it cost around $130m, some four times the cost of London's critically acclaimed 2012 offering.\", \"from\": 1017, \"to\": 1133, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1021, \"end\": 1027, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9982286822133913, \"rank\": 0.001532031831421299, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1089, \"end\": 1095, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.999894729297719, \"rank\": 0.00010528178184494273, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"around $130m\", \"from\": 1047, \"to\": 1059}, {\"ngram\": \"some four times the cost\", \"from\": 1061, \"to\": 1085}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Where was the money spent?\", \"from\": 1134, \"to\": 1160, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the money\", \"from\": 1144, \"to\": 1153}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The performances took place on a bridge over the River Seine, around a table that doubled as a catwalk.\", \"from\": 1162, \"to\": 1265, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1211, \"end\": 1222, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The performances\", \"from\": 1162, \"to\": 1178}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 1184, \"to\": 1189}, {\"ngram\": \"a bridge\", \"from\": 1193, \"to\": 1201}, {\"ngram\": \"a table\", \"from\": 1231, \"to\": 1238}, {\"ngram\": \"a catwalk\", \"from\": 1255, \"to\": 1264}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Parisian models, dancers, fashionistas and drag queens adorned the table.\", \"from\": 1266, \"to\": 1339, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Parisian models\", \"from\": 1266, \"to\": 1281}, {\"ngram\": \"dancers\", \"from\": 1283, \"to\": 1290}, {\"ngram\": \"fashionistas\", \"from\": 1292, \"to\": 1304}, {\"ngram\": \"drag queens\", \"from\": 1309, \"to\": 1320}, {\"ngram\": \"the table\", \"from\": 1329, \"to\": 1338}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the centre of it all was Barbara Butch, a plus-size lesbian DJ, clad in a sequinned blue dress and a golden, halo-style crown.\", \"from\": 1340, \"to\": 1469, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1368, \"end\": 1381, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"score\": 0.9999897744159937, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Barbara Butch\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\"}, {\"begin\": 1395, \"end\": 1402, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lesbian\", \"score\": 0.9999424491274274, \"rank\": 5.492067219879e-05, \"text\": \"lesbian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lesbian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lesbian\"}, {\"begin\": 1403, \"end\": 1405, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disc_jockey\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.096273487844868e-13, \"text\": \"DJ\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disc_jockey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Disc_jockey\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the centre\", \"from\": 1343, \"to\": 1353}, {\"ngram\": \"a sequinned blue dress\", \"from\": 1415, \"to\": 1437}, {\"ngram\": \"a golden, halo-style crown\", \"from\": 1442, \"to\": 1468}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At first sight, what was before us appeared to be a recreation of the biblical scene of Christ and his 12 apostles sharing a last meal before his crucifixion by a bunch of drag queens.\", \"from\": 1471, \"to\": 1655, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"first sight\", \"from\": 1474, \"to\": 1485}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 1503, \"to\": 1505}, {\"ngram\": \"a recreation\", \"from\": 1521, \"to\": 1533}, {\"ngram\": \"the biblical scene\", \"from\": 1537, \"to\": 1555}, {\"ngram\": \"Christ\", \"from\": 1559, \"to\": 1565}, {\"ngram\": \"his 12 apostles\", \"from\": 1570, \"to\": 1585}, {\"ngram\": \"a last meal\", \"from\": 1594, \"to\": 1605}, {\"ngram\": \"his crucifixion\", \"from\": 1613, \"to\": 1628}, {\"ngram\": \"a bunch\", \"from\": 1632, \"to\": 1639}, {\"ngram\": \"drag queens\", \"from\": 1643, \"to\": 1654}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There was a transgender model, a near-naked Greek god of wine, and music by DJ Butch: a woman who, by virtue of being proudly Jewish, fat and a lesbian, ticked a lot of boxes in the A-Z of \\\"inclusivity\\\", which appeared to be the primary theme of this year's ceremony.\", \"from\": 1656, \"to\": 1923, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1700, \"end\": 1705, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"score\": 0.889648554017175, \"rank\": 0.11059127060071063, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\"}, {\"begin\": 1782, \"end\": 1788, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judaism\", \"score\": 0.9996054035223213, \"rank\": 0.0003947521838255133, \"text\": \"Jewish\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judaism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Judaism\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a transgender model\", \"from\": 1666, \"to\": 1685}, {\"ngram\": \"wine\", \"from\": 1713, \"to\": 1717}, {\"ngram\": \"music\", \"from\": 1723, \"to\": 1728}, {\"ngram\": \"DJ Butch\", \"from\": 1732, \"to\": 1740}, {\"ngram\": \"a woman\", \"from\": 1742, \"to\": 1749}, {\"ngram\": \"virtue\", \"from\": 1758, \"to\": 1764}, {\"ngram\": \"a lesbian\", \"from\": 1798, \"to\": 1807}, {\"ngram\": \"a lot\", \"from\": 1816, \"to\": 1821}, {\"ngram\": \"boxes\", \"from\": 1825, \"to\": 1830}, {\"ngram\": \"the A-Z\", \"from\": 1834, \"to\": 1841}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"inclusivity\", \"from\": 1845, \"to\": 1857}, {\"ngram\": \"the primary theme\", \"from\": 1881, \"to\": 1898}, {\"ngram\": \"this year's ceremony\", \"from\": 1902, \"to\": 1922}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Butch, whose style was more drag queen than feminist, was in my opinion still the best thing on that stage, as she was at least an actual woman rather than some bloke portraying - or parodying - one.\", \"from\": 1925, \"to\": 2124, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Butch\", \"from\": 1925, \"to\": 1930}, {\"ngram\": \"whose style\", \"from\": 1932, \"to\": 1943}, {\"ngram\": \"more drag queen\", \"from\": 1948, \"to\": 1963}, {\"ngram\": \"feminist\", \"from\": 1969, \"to\": 1977}, {\"ngram\": \"my opinion\", \"from\": 1986, \"to\": 1996}, {\"ngram\": \"the best thing\", \"from\": 2003, \"to\": 2017}, {\"ngram\": \"that stage\", \"from\": 2021, \"to\": 2031}, {\"ngram\": \"at least an actual woman\", \"from\": 2044, \"to\": 2068}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Butch has since revealed some behind-the-scenes details about the opening ceremony, including that the idea behind the tableau was to \\\"celebrate love, inclusivity, diversity through music and dance to unite all of us\\\".\", \"from\": 2125, \"to\": 2343, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Butch\", \"from\": 2125, \"to\": 2130}, {\"ngram\": \"the-scenes\", \"from\": 2162, \"to\": 2172}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 2187, \"to\": 2207}, {\"ngram\": \"the idea\", \"from\": 2224, \"to\": 2232}, {\"ngram\": \"the tableau\", \"from\": 2240, \"to\": 2251}, {\"ngram\": \"love\", \"from\": 2270, \"to\": 2274}, {\"ngram\": \"inclusivity\", \"from\": 2276, \"to\": 2287}, {\"ngram\": \"diversity\", \"from\": 2289, \"to\": 2298}, {\"ngram\": \"music\", \"from\": 2307, \"to\": 2312}, {\"ngram\": \"dance\", \"from\": 2317, \"to\": 2322}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 2339, \"to\": 2341}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This tableau supposedly aimed at \\\"uniting\\\" people also included a blue Dionysus - Greek god of wine, festivity and fertility - portrayed by French singer Philippe Katerine, who laid naked on a platter among the drag queens.\", \"from\": 2345, \"to\": 2568, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2416, \"end\": 2424, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.796759558717506e-29, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}, {\"begin\": 2427, \"end\": 2432, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"score\": 0.889648554017175, \"rank\": 0.11059127060071063, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\"}, {\"begin\": 2485, \"end\": 2491, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9982286822133913, \"rank\": 0.001532031831421299, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2499, \"end\": 2516, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippe_Katerine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Philippe Katerine\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippe_Katerine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippe_Katerine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This tableau\", \"from\": 2345, \"to\": 2357}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"uniting\\\" people\", \"from\": 2378, \"to\": 2394}, {\"ngram\": \"wine\", \"from\": 2440, \"to\": 2444}, {\"ngram\": \"festivity\", \"from\": 2446, \"to\": 2455}, {\"ngram\": \"fertility\", \"from\": 2460, \"to\": 2469}, {\"ngram\": \"a platter\", \"from\": 2536, \"to\": 2545}, {\"ngram\": \"the drag queens\", \"from\": 2552, \"to\": 2567}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to the International Olympic Committee, this performance by what was essentially a man dressed as a Smurf was aimed at making us realise \\\"the absurdity of violence between human beings\\\".\", \"from\": 2569, \"to\": 2765, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2586, \"end\": 2617, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a man\", \"from\": 2660, \"to\": 2665}, {\"ngram\": \"a Smurf\", \"from\": 2677, \"to\": 2684}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 2705, \"to\": 2707}, {\"ngram\": \"the absurdity\", \"from\": 2717, \"to\": 2730}, {\"ngram\": \"violence\", \"from\": 2734, \"to\": 2742}, {\"ngram\": \"human beings\", \"from\": 2751, \"to\": 2763}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The ceremony, watched by over 28 million people, certainly managed to unite millions of people, just not in love and celebration, but disappointment and anger.\", \"from\": 2767, \"to\": 2926, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The ceremony\", \"from\": 2767, \"to\": 2779}, {\"ngram\": \"over 28 million people\", \"from\": 2792, \"to\": 2814}, {\"ngram\": \"millions\", \"from\": 2843, \"to\": 2851}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 2855, \"to\": 2861}, {\"ngram\": \"love\", \"from\": 2875, \"to\": 2879}, {\"ngram\": \"celebration\", \"from\": 2884, \"to\": 2895}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The French Catholic Church went berserk about what they saw as a parody of the Last Supper, and by extension, their entire religion.\", \"from\": 2928, \"to\": 3060, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2932, \"end\": 2954, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church_in_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French Catholic Church\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church_in_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church_in_France\"}, {\"begin\": 2939, \"end\": 2954, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999999943638613, \"rank\": 5.613088271747497e-09, \"text\": \"Catholic Church\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a parody\", \"from\": 2991, \"to\": 2999}, {\"ngram\": \"the Last Supper\", \"from\": 3003, \"to\": 3018}, {\"ngram\": \"extension\", \"from\": 3027, \"to\": 3036}, {\"ngram\": \"their entire religion\", \"from\": 3038, \"to\": 3059}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Christian conservatives in Europe and America, and even their Muslim counterparts across the world, followed suit expressing their outrage.\", \"from\": 3061, \"to\": 3200, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3061, \"end\": 3070, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999537013768279, \"rank\": 4.630076682378005e-05, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 3123, \"end\": 3129, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\", \"score\": 0.601326080163474, \"rank\": 0.6629912338405886, \"text\": \"Muslim\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Europe\", \"from\": 3088, \"to\": 3094}, {\"ngram\": \"America\", \"from\": 3099, \"to\": 3106}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 3150, \"to\": 3159}, {\"ngram\": \"suit\", \"from\": 3170, \"to\": 3174}, {\"ngram\": \"their outrage\", \"from\": 3186, \"to\": 3199}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The show was branded \\\"blasphemous\\\" and \\\"an abomination\\\".\", \"from\": 3201, \"to\": 3257, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The show\", \"from\": 3201, \"to\": 3209}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"blasphemous\\\" and \\\"an abomination\", \"from\": 3222, \"to\": 3255}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There were calls for boycotts from Latin America to the Middle East.\", \"from\": 3258, \"to\": 3326, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"calls\", \"from\": 3269, \"to\": 3274}, {\"ngram\": \"boycotts\", \"from\": 3279, \"to\": 3287}, {\"ngram\": \"Latin America\", \"from\": 3293, \"to\": 3306}, {\"ngram\": \"the Middle East\", \"from\": 3310, \"to\": 3325}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To so many, the expensive, poorly performed extravaganza on the Seine was an insult to everything they consider sacred.\", \"from\": 3327, \"to\": 3446, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3391, \"end\": 3396, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999999049578, \"rank\": 9.21345378160635e-11, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the expensive, poorly performed extravaganza\", \"from\": 3339, \"to\": 3383}, {\"ngram\": \"an insult\", \"from\": 3401, \"to\": 3410}, {\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 3414, \"to\": 3424}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Further, some suggested the tableau in Paris was not even a parody of Leonardo da Vinci's famous \\\"Last Supper\\\" painting, but was intended to be a recreation of \\\"The Feast of the Gods\\\" by Jan van Bijlert.\", \"from\": 3448, \"to\": 3651, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3487, \"end\": 3492, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.715056926133325e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 3518, \"end\": 3535, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.074985423695449e-31, \"text\": \"Leonardo da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}, {\"begin\": 3635, \"end\": 3650, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jan_van_Bijlert\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jan van Bijlert\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jan_van_Bijlert\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jan_van_Bijlert\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the tableau\", \"from\": 3472, \"to\": 3483}, {\"ngram\": \"even a parody\", \"from\": 3501, \"to\": 3514}, {\"ngram\": \"a recreation\", \"from\": 3592, \"to\": 3604}, {\"ngram\": \"The Feast\", \"from\": 3609, \"to\": 3618}, {\"ngram\": \"the Gods\", \"from\": 3622, \"to\": 3630}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That said, even if we accept, as the Olympic Committee suggested in the apology it offered to outraged Catholics, that the show had no intention of \\\"showing disrespect\\\" or parodying \\\"any religious group\\\", there is still reason for disappointment and anger, because there is no question in my mind that the show was parodying women.\", \"from\": 3653, \"to\": 3984, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3756, \"end\": 3765, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999999999054126, \"rank\": 5.6772698782547034e-11, \"text\": \"Catholics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Committee\", \"from\": 3686, \"to\": 3707}, {\"ngram\": \"the apology\", \"from\": 3721, \"to\": 3732}, {\"ngram\": \"the show\", \"from\": 3772, \"to\": 3780}, {\"ngram\": \"no intention\", \"from\": 3785, \"to\": 3797}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"any religious group\", \"from\": 3835, \"to\": 3855}, {\"ngram\": \"reason\", \"from\": 3873, \"to\": 3879}, {\"ngram\": \"disappointment\", \"from\": 3884, \"to\": 3898}, {\"ngram\": \"anger\", \"from\": 3903, \"to\": 3908}, {\"ngram\": \"no question\", \"from\": 3927, \"to\": 3938}, {\"ngram\": \"my mind\", \"from\": 3942, \"to\": 3949}, {\"ngram\": \"the show\", \"from\": 3955, \"to\": 3963}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 3978, \"to\": 3983}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Indeed, I am sick and tired of drag and the media and the entertainment world's seemingly never-ending obsession with it.\", \"from\": 3986, \"to\": 4107, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"drag\", \"from\": 4017, \"to\": 4021}, {\"ngram\": \"the media\", \"from\": 4026, \"to\": 4035}, {\"ngram\": \"the entertainment world's seemingly never-ending obsession\", \"from\": 4040, \"to\": 4098}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I have had enough of men parading around as caricatures of women, and everyone \\\"celebrating\\\" their \\\"art\\\", not realising how offensive this all is.\", \"from\": 4108, \"to\": 4254, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"men\", \"from\": 4129, \"to\": 4132}, {\"ngram\": \"caricatures\", \"from\": 4152, \"to\": 4163}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 4167, \"to\": 4172}, {\"ngram\": \"everyone\", \"from\": 4178, \"to\": 4186}, {\"ngram\": \"their \\\"art\", \"from\": 4201, \"to\": 4211}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was enraging to see it take centre stage at an event that is supposed to bring peoples of the world together, and according to the organisers' own testimony, celebrate love and inclusion.\", \"from\": 4255, \"to\": 4445, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"centre stage\", \"from\": 4286, \"to\": 4298}, {\"ngram\": \"an event\", \"from\": 4302, \"to\": 4310}, {\"ngram\": \"peoples\", \"from\": 4337, \"to\": 4344}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 4348, \"to\": 4357}, {\"ngram\": \"the organisers' own testimony\", \"from\": 4385, \"to\": 4414}, {\"ngram\": \"love\", \"from\": 4426, \"to\": 4430}, {\"ngram\": \"inclusion\", \"from\": 4435, \"to\": 4444}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When people look at minstrel shows of the past caricaturing enslaved Blacks, they immediately see there is no art to them - they are horrifically racist and insulting.\", \"from\": 4447, \"to\": 4614, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 4452, \"to\": 4458}, {\"ngram\": \"minstrel shows\", \"from\": 4467, \"to\": 4481}, {\"ngram\": \"the past caricaturing\", \"from\": 4485, \"to\": 4506}, {\"ngram\": \"Blacks\", \"from\": 4516, \"to\": 4522}, {\"ngram\": \"no art\", \"from\": 4554, \"to\": 4560}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But somehow, no one seems able to see how similarly insulting drag is to women.\", \"from\": 4615, \"to\": 4694, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no one\", \"from\": 4628, \"to\": 4634}, {\"ngram\": \"drag\", \"from\": 4677, \"to\": 4681}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 4688, \"to\": 4693}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Catholics accused the Olympic opening ceremony organisers and performers of disrespect towards the Church, but I honestly think that women were the ones being mocked and ridiculed on the global stage last Friday.\", \"from\": 4696, \"to\": 4908, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4696, \"end\": 4705, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999999999054126, \"rank\": 5.6772698782547034e-11, \"text\": \"Catholics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympic opening ceremony organisers\", \"from\": 4714, \"to\": 4753}, {\"ngram\": \"performers\", \"from\": 4758, \"to\": 4768}, {\"ngram\": \"the Church\", \"from\": 4791, \"to\": 4801}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 4829, \"to\": 4834}, {\"ngram\": \"the ones\", \"from\": 4840, \"to\": 4848}, {\"ngram\": \"the global stage\", \"from\": 4879, \"to\": 4895}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As a country, France is rightly proud of its artistic freedom but, to me, this ceremony reflected and perpetuated the misogyny within French culture.\", \"from\": 4910, \"to\": 5059, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4924, \"end\": 4930, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.6214450630094944, \"rank\": 0.6074441698549157, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 5044, \"end\": 5058, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French culture\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a country\", \"from\": 4913, \"to\": 4922}, {\"ngram\": \"its artistic freedom\", \"from\": 4951, \"to\": 4971}, {\"ngram\": \"this ceremony\", \"from\": 4984, \"to\": 4997}, {\"ngram\": \"the misogyny\", \"from\": 5024, \"to\": 5036}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I do not think it set a good tone for how the Olympics views women.\", \"from\": 5060, \"to\": 5127, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a good tone\", \"from\": 5082, \"to\": 5093}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 5102, \"to\": 5114}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 5121, \"to\": 5126}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We are only a few days in and already there has been controversy over certain male fans complaining that female beach volleyball players have been allowed to reject the bikini bottoms they were previously required to wear - with the International Olympic Committee even mandating how skimpy they had to be - in favour of leggings.\", \"from\": 5128, \"to\": 5458, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5361, \"end\": 5392, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"only a few days\", \"from\": 5135, \"to\": 5150}, {\"ngram\": \"controversy\", \"from\": 5181, \"to\": 5192}, {\"ngram\": \"certain male fans\", \"from\": 5198, \"to\": 5215}, {\"ngram\": \"that female beach volleyball players\", \"from\": 5228, \"to\": 5264}, {\"ngram\": \"the bikini bottoms\", \"from\": 5293, \"to\": 5311}, {\"ngram\": \"favour\", \"from\": 5439, \"to\": 5445}, {\"ngram\": \"leggings\", \"from\": 5449, \"to\": 5457}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Over the years, there have been numerous controversies surrounding the Olympic Games, from allegations of sexism and cultural relativism to just plain mismanagement.\", \"from\": 5460, \"to\": 5625, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the years\", \"from\": 5465, \"to\": 5474}, {\"ngram\": \"numerous controversies\", \"from\": 5492, \"to\": 5514}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 5527, \"to\": 5544}, {\"ngram\": \"allegations\", \"from\": 5551, \"to\": 5562}, {\"ngram\": \"sexism\", \"from\": 5566, \"to\": 5572}, {\"ngram\": \"cultural relativism\", \"from\": 5577, \"to\": 5596}, {\"ngram\": \"just plain mismanagement\", \"from\": 5600, \"to\": 5624}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But as far as I am concerned, the opening ceremony in Paris this year was conspicuous for its mediocracy.\", \"from\": 5626, \"to\": 5731, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5680, \"end\": 5685, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.715056926133325e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 5656, \"to\": 5676}, {\"ngram\": \"its mediocracy\", \"from\": 5716, \"to\": 5730}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It obviously tried very hard to represent an inclusive culture, but it ended up looking like a drunken fight in a fairground.\", \"from\": 5732, \"to\": 5857, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an inclusive culture\", \"from\": 5774, \"to\": 5794}, {\"ngram\": \"a drunken fight\", \"from\": 5825, \"to\": 5840}, {\"ngram\": \"a fairground\", \"from\": 5844, \"to\": 5856}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The views expressed in this article are the author's own and do not necessarily reflect Al Jazeera's editorial stance.\", \"from\": 5859, \"to\": 5977, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5947, \"end\": 5957, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\", \"score\": 0.99999989970866, \"rank\": 1.0028068350026307e-07, \"text\": \"Al Jazeera\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Al_Jazeera\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The views\", \"from\": 5859, \"to\": 5868}, {\"ngram\": \"this article\", \"from\": 5882, \"to\": 5894}, {\"ngram\": \"the author\", \"from\": 5899, \"to\": 5909}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow Al Jazeera English:\", \"from\": 5997, \"to\": 6023, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Follow Al Jazeera English\", \"from\": 5997, \"to\": 6022}]}]}"